Locator Techniques

CSS Selector:

<button class="submit signInBtn" type="submit">Sign In</button>
<input type="text" placeholder="Username" id="inputUsername" value="">

1. Class name -> tagname.classname --> button.submit signInBtn
2. ID -> tagname#ID --> input#InputName

When css selector does not have class name or id:
Then you will have a generic attribute --> tagname[attribute='value']
And attribute value should be unique    ---> input[placeholder='Username']